article.headline: Six Minnesota players score in double figures
article.linkText: Garnett leads Timberwolves to 8th straight win
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Kevin Garnett scored 26 points to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 99-96 victory over the Atlanta Hawks in an exhibition game Thursday night. Latrell Sprewell, who played at Alabama, scored 10 points for Minnesota but was sidelined for the second half with a tender ankle. Antoine Walker had 22 points and Jon Barry added 16 for the Hawks, who trailed by as many as 14 points in the third quarter before cutting the deficit to one late in the fourth quarter. Walker missed an off-balance 3-point try as time ran out in regulation. Garnett had 10 points and Sprewell added eight as Minnesota (1-1) took a 32-18 lead after one quarter. Chris Crawford scored nine points in the second quarter as Atlanta (1-1) got within 47-40 at halftime. Garnett scored all the points in a 10-0 run that gave the Timberwolves a 64-50 lead midway through the third quarter. With 3:16 left in the third, Garnett fouled Crawford as he tried to convert a steal into a transition basket. Crawford injured his right knee and was helped off the floor. He is scheduled to have an MRI on Friday in Atlanta.
